1 Install github to in your computer
Follow below steps:

https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-Installing-Git


2 Create account in github https://github.com
3 Create project in github
4 Before working with repository, you need to configure your github username and email ID by running below command

$ git config --global --edit

name = tenzindorji
email = niznetij@gmail.com

5 Create local directory where you can check out the repository
6 Create atleast one file so that it doesn't fail when you commit and push to github
9 Initialize the local directory as a Git repository
 $ git init
10 Add the files in the local repository and stages them for commit. To unstage a file, use 'git reset HEAD YOUR-FILE'.

  $ git add .

11 Commit the files that you've staged in your local repository.

  $ git commit -m "First commit"
 12 Connect to github remove repository
 Example: git remote add origin https://github.com/tenzindorji/myjenkinsproject.git

  $ git remote add origin remote_repository_URL

 13 Push the changes in your local repository to GitHub. Enter github username and password

  $ git push origin master

 14 Check the files uploaded in github.com

Rails setup

rails new projectname

Controllers and views
rails generate 




Docker Container: Commands
docker run --rm busybox:latest /bin/echo "hello world"
docker images
docker ps -a
docker rm "container ID/first few words of container ID"
docker rmi "image id" # rmi to effect image ids
docker run -it --rm busybox:latest # get into busy box shell

docker run -d -p 80:80 --name webserver nginx